Stunica continued at Rome his attacks upon Erasmus' workÍ¾ and in consequence his name appears frequently in Erasmus' correspondence, with great obloquy. But after some years better feeling prevailed: and instead of pub- lishing the criticisms which he had made upon Erasmus' fourth edition of the New Testament, 1527, Stunica proposed to commu- nicate them to him privately.
